# WhatsApp template playbook (MSG91)

Use this when adding or changing **approved WhatsApp templates** and wiring them in EaseMySalon. For the short checklist, see **`whatsapp-integration.mdc`**.

---

## 1. Design the template before coding

1. **Choose a camelCase template type key** (e.g. `clientWalletTransaction`). It becomes:
   - `AdminSettings.notifications.whatsapp.templates.<key>` (template ID string)
   - `templateVariables.<key>` / `templateJavaScriptCodes.<key>`
   - `whatsappService.send<Name>()` often uses the same string in `getTemplateId('<key>')` and `mapDataToTemplateVariables('<key>', data)`.

2. **Lock the variable count** in Meta / MSG91 first. Body placeholders `{{1}}`…`{{N}}` map to API `body_1`…`body_n`. **N must match** what the backend sends after mapping. Extra or missing variables → **silent non-delivery** (API may still return success).

3. **Name data fields** the backend will populate (snake-free camelCase): e.g. `clientName`, `planName`, `amountFormatted`. Document them in the playbook section of your PR or in this rule’s “Field contract” for that template.

4. **Avoid redundant copy** in the template body (e.g. don’t repeat “prepaid wallet” if `{{2}}` is already the plan name).

---

## 2. Field contract (payload → template)

| Step | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| Caller / `send-*-whatsapp.js` | Builds a plain `data` object: every **mapped** field should be a string (or coerced before send). |
| `whatsappService.send*` | Merges `...rest` into `data`, calls `mapDataToTemplateVariables(templateType, data)`. |
| `mapDataToTemplateVariables` | Uses `AdminSettings.notifications.whatsapp.templateVariables[templateType]`: keys `body_1`, `body_2`, … values = **names of keys on `data`**. |
| **Fallback** (no admin mapping) | If `Object.keys(variables).length === 0`, `send*` must set `body_1`…`body_n` explicitly — **same n as MSG91 template**. |

---

## 3. Code touch list (new transactional template)

Do **all** that apply. Order helps avoid “template ID saved but nowhere to send”.

### Schema & defaults

| Area | File / action |
|------|----------------|
| Template ID slot | `backend/models/AdminSettings.js` → `notifications.whatsapp.templates.<newKey>: { type: String, default: '' }` |
| New admin preference (optional) | Same file → e.g. `notifications.whatsapp.<feature>Notifications: Mixed` with `{ enabled: true }` |
| Merge existing DB docs | `adminSettingsSchema.statics.getSettings` → `waDefaultTemplateIds` / similar loop so old installs get the new key |
| WhatsApp log enum (if new) | `backend/models/WhatsAppMessageLog.js` → `messageType.enum` |

### Service

| Area | File / action |
|------|----------------|
| Send API | `backend/services/whatsapp-service.js` → `async send<Feature>(payload)` using `getTemplateId('<newKey>')`, `mapDataToTemplateVariables`, **fallback `body_*` count = MSG91** |
| Test send | Same file → `testConnection`: for each `dataField` in variable mapping, add a branch in the test-value generator so **Test WhatsApp** in admin works |

### Gates & business settings (if per-salon toggle)

| Area | File / action |
|------|----------------|
| Admin gate helper | `backend/lib/whatsapp-admin-gates.js` → `isAdmin<Feature>NotificationsEnabled` using `isAdminWhatsappPreferenceTrueByDefault` |
| Defaults merge | `backend/lib/whatsapp-settings-defaults.js` + `backend/routes/email-notifications.js` GET/PUT merge for `whatsappNotificationSettings` |
| Salon UI | `components/settings/whatsapp-business-settings.tsx` |

### Reusable sender (recommended)

| Area | File / action |
|------|----------------|
| Sender module | `backend/lib/send-<feature>-whatsapp.js` — init service, admin + business gates, quiet hours, `send*`, `WhatsAppMessageLog`, quota / `deductWhatsApp` |
| Wire after DB success | Route or service: `void send...().catch(...)` so WhatsApp never fails the main transaction |

### Admin UI (critical for operators)

**File:** `components/admin/admin-settings/whatsapp-admin-settings.tsx`

| Area | What to add |
|------|-------------|
| Initial `templates` state | `<newKey>: ""` |
| Test template `<SelectItem>` | So admin can pick type in “Test WhatsApp Configuration” |
| **`handleParseTemplateJson` `defaultFields`** | `<newKey>: ['field1', 'field2', ...]` in **field order** = `body_1`, `body_2`, … for auto-map |
| **`handleSaveEdit` inner `defaultFields`** | Same array (duplicate block in save path) |
| **Modal “Parse & Auto-Configure” `defaultFields`** | Same array (third duplicate) |
| **Variable mapping `<SelectContent>`** | Every value in `defaultFields` must appear as `<SelectItem value="fieldName">…</SelectItem>`. **If missing, dropdown shows blank for auto-mapped keys** (common bug). Prefer `templateType === '<newKey>'` block for template-specific fields so the list stays short for other templates. |

### Cross-links

- Receipt / appointment flows: `whatsapp-integration.mdc`
- Security / auth: `security.mdc` if the new endpoint is sensitive

