## 6. Verification checklist before merge

- [ ] MSG91 template approved; **body (and button) variable count** documented
- [ ] Fallback in `send*` assigns exactly that many `body_*` (and buttons if any)
- [ ] `AdminSettings` schema + `getSettings` merge include new template key
- [ ] All three `defaultFields` entries in `whatsapp-admin-settings.tsx` for the new key
- [ ] **Every** mapped field appears in the variable-mapping dropdown (or shared list covers it)
- [ ] `testConnection` returns sensible text for each mapped `dataField` (or generic `Test ${dataField}`)
- [ ] `WhatsAppMessageLog` enum updated if using a new `messageType`
- [ ] Manual test: Admin → Test WhatsApp → select template type → send to a test phone

---

## 7. Common mistakes

| Mistake | Symptom |
|---------|---------|
| Variable count ≠ template | Message never arrives; MSG91 may still report success |
| Auto-parse maps `body_2` → `planName` but no `SelectItem` for `planName` | Dropdown empty; hard to fix mapping in UI |
| New key not in `getSettings` merge | Existing production admin doc missing key; undefined behavior in UI |
| Forgetting `testConnection` branches | Test message sends wrong or empty slots |
| Using `=== true` on admin WhatsApp prefs | `undefined` reads as “off”; use `whatsapp-admin-gates` helpers |
